# Database & Data Management Rules

## 🗄️ Database Setup

- Use MongoDB + Prisma for data management
- Follow Prisma best practices for schema design
- Implement proper database relationships
- Use type-safe database operations

## 📊 Schema Design

- Design normalized database schemas
- Use proper indexing for performance
- Implement soft deletes where appropriate
- Handle data migrations carefully

## 🔄 Data Operations

- Use Prisma Client for all database operations
- Implement proper error handling for database queries
- Use transactions for complex operations
- Optimize queries for performance

## 🛡️ Data Security

- Validate all data before database operations
- Implement proper access controls
- Use environment variables for database credentials
- Regular database backups

## 📈 Performance

- Use database indexes strategically
- Implement query optimization
- Monitor database performance
- Use connection pooling appropriately

